&lt;Mitsui Investment Management Co Ltd>(MIMCL) and &lt;Alliance Capital Management International Inc>(ACMII) will sign an agreement late this month to cooperate ininternational fund management, a ACMII spokesman said.    MIMCL, 55-pct controlled by affiliated companies of MitsuiBank Ltd &lt;MIBT.T>, will reconsign some of its foreignsecurities investment orders to ACMII, he told Reuters.    ACMII, the London-based 100 pct-owned subsidiary of&lt;Alliance Capital Management Corp> of New York, will reconsignsome of its foreign orders to MIMCL and instruct MIMCL ininternational fund management techniques, the spokesman said.    Both firms were among 56 investment advisory companiesgranted Japanese government approval for discretionary fundmanagement on June 10, the Mitsui spokesman said.    Alliance Capital Management Corp is the world's biggestfirm devoted exclusively to fund management and has 35 billiondlrs in funds, he said.    Mitsui Investment Co Ltd, established two years ago,controls about 800 mln dlrs, 80 pct of which is invested inJapanese equities. REUTER&#3;